text.section:
Subject to the provisions of subsection (b) of this section, the Commission may order summarily the suspension of the license of a licensee if the licensee:
fails to account promptly for any money held in trust;
on demand, fails to display to the Commission all records, books, and accounts of any money held in trust;
has been convicted of a felony under the laws of the United States or of any state; or
within 10 days after the conviction or within 10 days following release from incarceration as a result of the conviction, whichever is later, fails to disclose to the Commission that the licensee has been convicted of a felony under the laws of the United States or of any state.
